results.name: Greatest semiprime divisor of n-th composite number.
link: Zak Seidov, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..1000
mathematica: Reap[Do[If[! PrimeQ[n], fl = Flatten[Table[#[[1]], {#[[2]]}] & /@ FactorInteger[n]]; Sow[fl[[-1]]*fl[[-2]]]], {n, 4, 1200}]][[2, 1]]; (* _Zak Seidov_, Mar 18 2013 *)
